Tingstjg. i Linköp. domis. 29-32, tjg. i Svea hovr. 32-33, egen adv:verks. i Linköp. fr. 33. V. krigsfiskal v. Livgren: reg., Svea trängkår, Ostgöta luftv:reg. o. Östg. flygflottilj fr. 36. Led. av styr. f. Skandinavbankens Linköp :kont., suppl. i styr. f. A-B Stora Hotellet, f. Lin-köp. Teater A-B m. fl. Tj :man i fl. ordenssällsk. o. klubbar.
translated: Åby, Östergötland, 1st, son of landowner Axel Andersson and Anna Åström. Married in 1946 to Britt Sundin. - Studied: graduated from high school in Linköping in 1923, obtained a law degree in Uppsala in 1929. Served as a court official in Linköping from 1929-1932, worked in the Svea Court of Appeal from 1932-1933, and had his own law practice in Linköping from 1933. Served as a military prosecutor in the Life Grenadier Regiment, Svea Service Corps, Östergötland Air Force Regiment, and Östergötland Air Force Squadron from 1936. Member of the board for Skandinavbanken in Linköping, and a substitute board member for A-B Stora Hotellet, Lin-köp. Theater A-B, and others. Also a member of various orders and clubs.
